    <div class="tip-box">
      <span class="tip-box-ico">&#128161;</span>
      <p><strong>Label reading tip:</strong> Always look for the DHA-specific dose on the supplement facts panel, not just "total omega-3." A product claiming 500mg omega-3 may contain only 100mg DHA — the rest could be EPA, ALA, or other fatty acids that do not serve the same neurodevelopmental function. DHA is the omega-3 that matters most during pregnancy.</p>
    </div>

